## 4) Documentation Sync Gate (Required)

If behavior changes, update docs in the same session:

1. Update the canonical source from the ownership map.
2. Update any rule/reference summary that points to that topic.
3. Remove stale names when features are renamed/removed.
4. Finish by verifying no contradictory instructions remain between:
   - `llms.txt`
   - `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`
   - `.cursor/commands/*.md`
   - `docs/**`, `design/**`, and `.cursor/docs/studio/**` where studio coordination applies

## 5) Definition of Done (Engine Changes)

- Code behavior is complete and coherent.
- Canonical doc updated for changed behavior.
- Derived summaries/rules updated where referenced.
- Architecture checklist passes (`.cursor/commands/check-architecture.md`).
- Playtest docs remain consistent (`.cursor/rules/ai-playtesting.mdc` and `.cursor/commands/playtest.md`).
